Package view

Contains the classes that build the visual layer of the app
  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    ConfigLoadNotifier
    Used to charge configuration values on the view
    DeleteUserNotifier
    Interface used for actions regarding user deletion
    KeyChanger
    Interface used for when a note is assigned a new character
    LogInNotifier
    Interfaced used to notify about the results of log in and register
    NewPlayNotifier
    Interface tasked with reloading the graph's information when the user generates a new play
    PianoNotifier
    Manages actions regarding the piano keys
    PlayingSongNotifier
    Manages when a new song is playing
    PlaylistMenuNotifier
    Notifies playlist related actions, such as deletions and insertions
    SongsMenuNotifier
    Notifies song related actions, such as deletions and insertions
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    BottomPanel
    Class with the bottom panel functionalities for song playing
    ChangeKeyButton
    Button used to change the user's binging to the piano keys
    CreatePlaylistPopUp
    Pop up that asks for the name of the playlist being created
    GenericButton
    Custom button used widely on the app
    GraphDrawer
    Class used to draw the graphs
    LogIn
    Window used for user Log in and Registration, the user can switch between both screens
    Menu
    JFrame that contains everything in the app once the user has logged in
    Piano
    Class that contains the piano keys, the note bindings and some extra buttons
    Playlist
    Initializes the panel of the "Playlists" tab and implements its functionalities
    Ranking
    Initializes the "Ranking" tab, sets up the graphs, table, and implements the functionalities
    Settings
    Initializes the "Settings" tab, and implements its functionalities
    Songs
    Initializes the "Songs" tab, and implements its functionalities
    Tecla
    Class that constitutes the piano and reacts to the user's input, can be of two types: black and white
    Top5Drawer
    Draws and fills the "top 5 songs" table
    UneditableTable
    Custom default table model that can't be edited by the user
  • Enum Summary
    Enum Description
    ColorConstants
    Defines color constants commonly used
    Icon
    Defines several ASCII characters that are used like icons
